ebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Net::SMTP is vulnerable to RCPT TO/MAIL FROM injection due to lack of input validation and conformance to the SMTP protocol.\n\nPublicly disclosed already: http://www.mbsd.jp/Whitepaper/smtpi.pdf\n\nPeople are wrongly assigning this to the mail gem (http://rubysec.com/advisories/OSVDB-131677/) and thinking it's fixed, when in fact the underlying vuln remains in Net::SMTP.\n\nDiscussed as an issue with the `mail` library here: https://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215. And mentioned that it's likely an issue with net-smtp not doing input validation, per RFC spec: https://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215#issuecomment-163906956\n\nThe mail gem *should* do input validation too, of course. But its responsibility is creating internet messages, and it would validate addresses against that spec. Its responsibility is not SMTP protocol compliance. Net::SMTP is.\n\nAddressing this in Ruby in a timely manner will help resolve the considerable confusion that's emerged due to the lack of response to a publicly disclosed vulnerability.","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eNet::SMTP is vulnerable to RCPT TO/MAIL FROM injection due to lack of input validation and conformance to the SMTP protocol.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePublicly disclosed already: \u003ca title=\"http://www.mbsd.jp/Whitepaper/smtpi.pdf\" href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mbsd.jp%2FWhitepaper%2Fsmtpi.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttp://www.mbsd.jp/Whitepaper/smtpi.pdf\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePeople are wrongly assigning this to the mail gem (\u003ca title=\"http://rubysec.com/advisories/OSVDB-131677/\" href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Frubysec.com%2Fadvisories%2FOSVDB-131677%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttp://rubysec.com/advisories/OSVDB-131677/\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e) and thinking it\u0026#39;s fixed, when in fact the underlying vuln remains in Net::SMTP.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDiscussed as an issue with the \u003ccode\u003email\u003c/code\u003e library here: \u003ca title=\"https://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Frubysec%2Fruby-advisory-db%2Fissues%2F215\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. And mentioned that it\u0026#39;s likely an issue with net-smtp not doing input validation, per RFC spec: \u003ca title=\"https://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215#issuecomment-163906956\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Frubysec%2Fruby-advisory-db%2Fissues%2F215%23issuecomment-163906956\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://github.com/rubysec/ruby-advisory-db/issues/215#issuecomment-163906956\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe mail gem \u003cem\u003eshould\u003c/em\u003e do input validation too, of course. But its responsibility is creating internet messages, and it would validate addresses against that spec. Its responsibility is not SMTP protocol compliance. Net::SMTP is.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAddressing this in Ruby in a timely manner will help resolve the considerable confusion that\u0026#39;s emerged due to the lack of response to a publicly disclosed vulnerability.\u003c/p\u003e\n","weakness":{"id":58,"name":"Command Injection - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2016-07-23T04:09:31.831Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-139969046.20363098,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":9,"voters":["lukasreschke","eveeez","paulos_","silv3rpoision","paragonie-scott","dyabla","arice","pei","troysucks"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":963303,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi Jeremy,\n\nWe have a ticket about this in the private GitHub security repository.  I'm pasting the conversation below.\n\n@unak said:\n\nIMO, Net ::SMTP does not have to validate its inputs always.\nThis means that the library does not have to check whether the sender address is RFC5822 compliant or not.\nBut Net::BufferedIO#writeline may have to check the parameter does not contain CR and LF.\n\nThen @shugo said:\n\n\u003e IMO, Net ::SMTP does not have to validate its inputs always.\n\nAgreed.\n\n\u003e This means that the library does not have to check whether the sender address is RFC5822 compliant or not.\n\nIf Net::SMTP verify input, there's a consideration about source routing lists.\nThey should be rejected according to RFC5321.\n\n\u003e But Net::BufferedIO#writeline may have to check the parameter does not contain CR and LF.\n\nI'm not sure whether it should do.","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eHi Jeremy,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe have a ticket about this in the private GitHub security repository.  I\u0026#39;m pasting the conversation below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"/unak\"\u003e@unak\u003c/a\u003e said:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIMO, Net ::SMTP does not have to validate its inputs always.\u003cbr\u003e\nThis means that the library does not have to check whether the sender address is RFC5822 compliant or not.\u003cbr\u003e\nBut Net::BufferedIO#writeline may have to check the parameter does not contain CR and LF.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThen \u003ca href=\"/shugo\"\u003e@shugo\u003c/a\u003e said:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIMO, Net ::SMTP does not have to validate its inputs always.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAgreed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis means that the library does not have to check whether the sender address is RFC5822 compliant or not.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf Net::SMTP verify input, there\u0026#39;s a consideration about source routing lists.\u003cbr\u003e\nThey should be rejected according to RFC5321.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut Net::BufferedIO#writeline may have to check the parameter does not contain CR and LF.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;m not sure whether it should do.\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-05-18T15:45:55.314Z","updated_at":"2016-05-18T15:45:55.314Z","actor":{"username":"tenderlove","cleared":false,"url":"/tenderlove","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/318/60d828744b5d16813ecbf975fdc453dc4a933f4f_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"ruby","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":964010,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Agree it's not Net::SMTP's job to validate RFC5822 addresses.\n\nIt is Net::SMTP's job to [validate RFC5321 lines](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5321#section-2.3.8) and follow the [command argument syntax](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5321#section-4.1.2).\n\n\u003e SMTP client implementations **MUST NOT** transmit these characters except when they are intended as line terminators and then **MUST**, as indicated above, transmit them only as a \u003cCRLF\u003e sequence.","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eAgree it\u0026#39;s not Net::SMTP\u0026#39;s job to validate RFC5822 addresses.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt is Net::SMTP\u0026#39;s job to \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftools.ietf.org%2Fhtml%2Frfc5321%23section-2.3.8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003evalidate RFC5321 lines\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and follow the \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftools.ietf.org%2Fhtml%2Frfc5321%23section-4.1.2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ecommand argument syntax\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSMTP client implementations \u003cstrong\u003eMUST NOT\u003c/strong\u003e transmit these characters except when they are intended as line terminators and then \u003cstrong\u003eMUST\u003c/strong\u003e, as indicated above, transmit them only as a \u0026lt;CRLF\u0026gt; sequence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-05-18T22:40:12.933Z","updated_at":"2016-05-18T22:40:12.933Z","actor":{"username":"jeremy","cleared":false,"url":"/jeremy","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/121/d8d8bc5a99a5229118f3f1064beb83458d1d10d6_original.jpg/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"ruby","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1004104,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi Jeremy,\n\nI'd like to merge the attached patch as a normal bug fix.\nCould you check it?","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eHi Jeremy,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;d like to merge the attached patch as a normal bug fix.\u003cbr\u003e\nCould you check it?\u003